"The overall goal that the project ""Regions without Borders"" sets is to raise the awareness of Bulgarians about cohesion policies, as well as to make visible the direct benefits of the implementation of cohesion policies for specific regions, sectors and social groups.
The main thematic areas presented in the project cover the Cohesion Policies and the Just Transition Fund. Activities for raising awareness and popularization, as well as forms for feedback and direct participation of citizens and interested parties in the discussions initiated within the project, are foreseen. The project aims to reach the widest possible audience in the country.
The Proposal envisages the creation of copyrighted content in the “24 Chasa” newspaper, “168 Chasa” weekly, Club 100 weekly, “Cosmos” magazine, their online versions, social networks and platforms. The following project activities are included:
1. Creation and distribution of copyrighted video content;
2. Podcast: Broadcast of 7 episodes with interviews;
3. Content generation in print media – thematic pages, specialized print application;
4. Popularization of cohesion policies in online editions, news website and social networks;
6. Organizing special events with the participation of interested parties."

Il progetto mira alla realizzazione di un piano di comunicazione capace di dare la massima visibilità a tutte le opportunità offerte dalle Politiche di Coesione. Siamo consapevoli dell'importanza strategica della comunicazione per sensibilizzare i cittadini e partecipare alle politiche e ai programmi dell'UE. Una strategia di comunicazione efficace può avviare un circolo virtuoso che ridurrà le distanze, supererà lo scetticismo e aumenterà la conoscenza e l'interesse dei cittadini sulle istituzioni europee. L'attività informativa metterà in evidenza il valore aggiunto dell'intervento comunitario nelle politiche nazionali e regionali, mostrando il ruolo svolto dall'UE e dalle politiche di coesione nei processi di sviluppo. Gli obiettivi principali del progetto sono:
• Promuovere e facilitare una migliore comprensione del ruolo della politica di coesione nel fornire sostegno a tutte le regioni dell'UE;
• Migliorare la consapevolezza dell'impatto che la Politica di Coesione ha sullo sviluppo del territorio, evidenziando lo stretto legame tra i fondi comunitari, nazionali e regionali;
• Stimolare l'interesse e lo spirito di iniziativa dei cittadini attraverso la diffusione di storie di successo regionali ed europee realizzate con i fondi della politica di coesione;
Il progetto promuove azioni di comunicazione sulle le politiche di Coesione sia a livello nazionale che a livello regionale (Sicilia) attraverso lo Sport e con il mondo sportivo coinvolgendo anche la cittadinanza.
Principali attività:
• Campagna di comunicazione attraverso lo sport che si svolgerà sia a livello regionale (Sicilia) che nazionale, e avrà come testimonial due squadre di basket femminile (Famila Schio Veneto in serie A1 e Verga Basket di Palermo in serie B)
• Mostra itinerante presso palazzetti dello Sport, Palestre,centri Sportivi e nelle Scuole. Verrà realizzata una mostra composta da totem informativi sulle Politiche di Coesione.
• Video interviste ai cittadini.

The European Union’s Regional Policy represents one of the most important place-based programs in the world for the distribution of wealth between regions and countries. The Cohesion Policy in Italy represents the only instrument capable of reducing territorial gaps between northern and southern regions without reducing investments in the most advanced ones. Astonishing achievements have been achieved in the last decades in the field of ecology transitions, social inclusion, economic development, and research courtesy of the structural fund investments. However, Italian citizens seem not convinced of the impact of the policy on the socio-economic fabric yet and, even worse, they are not aware of its existence, although it has been ameliorating their life for 30 years.
To tackle these issues, the project BRanding, Informing and Disseminating the cohesion policy to General and Expert audience (BRIDGE) has been built upon two theoretical assumptions: citizens’ awareness is a condition sine qua non to build a long-lasting engagement and traditional online awareness campaigns should be improved by adopting an entertainment approach able to inform and entertainingly educate the audience without losing editorial authority. In doing so, the project has been split into 3 fundamental pillars:

1. Edutainment strategy to explain to citizens the Cohesion Policy 2021-27;
2. Infotainment strategy to promote the results of the Cohesion Policy 2014-20;
3. Capacity building for communication professionals to enhance online communication skills and strategies for systematically communicating the Cohesion Policy.

The 3 strategies will support the project in creating and disseminating information and contents in order to increase awareness and reduce scepticism on the EU Cohesion policy while strengthening the communication capacity of news media professionals in maximizing communication effectiveness of Cohesion Policy related contents.

The project “Europa, Italia” (EUIT) intends to design and implement an objective, transparent, comprehensive, targeted, multi-media, and multi-faceted information and communication campaign on the EU cohesion policy in Italy, with a focus on key priority themes such as job creation, climate change, digital transformation, and research and innovation.
Specifically, the project will:
1)inform at least 8 mil Italian citizens about the cohesion policy and its role in strengthening the European identity and in fostering the socio-economic development of all European regions;
2)enable at least 5 mil Italian citizens to increase their knowledge and awareness of the EU institutions, policies, and projects, as well as of how these impact on people’s lives;
3)directly engage at least 5,000 people (3,000 young people) in discussing and communicating about the cohesion policy, thus favouring a shared ownership of the European process;
4)strengthen the role of “Europa, Italia” (https://www.repubblica.it/dossier/esteri/fondi-strutturali-europei-progetti-italia/) as a primary web hub in Italy for information and communication about the EU. 
The project will create and implement a set of integrated information and communication outputs and services on the cohesion policy, including the management of the “Europa, Italia” webpage, 200 news items, 10 in-depth articles, two videos, 10 infographics, one podcasts series with six episodes, four webinars, one online and in-person event, as well as posts on social media pages, in order to reach out to, and engage the Italian general audience, young people, and stakeholders such as local/regional/national authorities and decision makers, media/journalists, business, and academia.
The project will do so via an innovative methodology featuring targeted communication strategy, diversified and tailor-made information channels and outputs, and multifocal storytelling, involving business, academia, institutional representatives, and beneficaries.

