The proposed Action envisages an innovative, holistic, interactive and diverse system of information and public engagement that will address the total of the Greek-speaking world and will bring citizens centre-stage, providing:

	• a full informative package about the achievements of Cohesion policies, employing all popular formats available (news, video, photo, mobile);
	• a forward-looking perspective into Cohesion policies focusing on their benefits in the next decade in the light of current and future challenges, such as the pandemic and the energy crisis emanating from the war in Ukraine, and the NextGenerationEU priorities;
	• an opportunity for citizens to have their voice heard, by recording their concerns and delivering the EU Cohesion policies responses to them.

The Action will harness ANA-MPA’s massive reach through all channels available to it, which offer unique access to practically the whole of Greece’s public opinion, notably including all regions and localities. Thus, this sustainable, measurable and value-for-money Action will:

	• raise awareness among the general public, opinion formers and stakeholders from government and the Regions about the EU’s impact on people’s lives through Cohesion projects;
	• highlight benefits particularly for the Regions;
	• foster public debate on the EU’s priorities that directly affect its peoples and the future challenges it faces;
	• stimulate citizen participation in the public discourse on all matters EU; and
	• counter the claim that the Union is merely a distant bureaucratic Leviathan.
